<a href="http://www.angelfire.com/rpg2/thedarkexile/" target="_blank">The Dark Exile</a> <BR> Warlord of the 7th Hammer <BR> <img src="http://www.clicksmilie.de/sammlung/musik/musik009.gif" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uchubbylumpkinsanklesbane.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chubbylumpkins Anklesbane</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 135<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/02 6:35:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3890.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Resists on Rage of Vallon</span><hr size=1> Pally proc is MR I think.<br>
<br>
RoV is FR, so a good chunk of mobs resist it due to their FR being high, like 95% of CT.<br>
<br>
It's always stuck well on ST golems though, other than a few fluke resists every now and again. Could have been bad luck.<br>
<br>
That said, so long as your not defensive, primal 2hs blows primal/red away for agro. Even with defensive it's a close call. <p><font size=2><font color=blue><a href=http://nightwatchers.dpn.ch/eq_view_profile.html?num=1190>Chubbylumpkins Anklesbane</a></font></font>
</BR>The last was plainly old Fatty Lumpkins: he was larger, stronger, fatter (and older)...</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ualien1099.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alien1099</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>will kick your @$$</span><br>  Posts: 491<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/15/02 5:15:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3890.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/~mondo/aliensm.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Resists on Rage of Vallon</span><hr size=1> No the proc used to land probably 90 percent of the time on most mobs except those that were fire immune. Now it's getting resisted by 90 percent of the mobs out there. The Paladin epic proc is fire based I believe, but it's also a lure. I just left a feedback suggesting it be turned into a lure type spell as well. <p><p><font face="verdana, arial" size="-2"><u><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=6885" target=top>Gerald Swiftblades</a></u> [<a href="http://" target=top><i></i></a>]<br>
      <b>Human Warlord</b><br>
      Solusek Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lythe>Lythe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 61<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/16/02 6:32:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3890.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Resists on Rage of Vallon</span><hr size=1> The fiery defender proc &quot;holy shock&quot; is MR based and with -100 resist modifier according to lucy.  That is the neg3 charisma lure1 level,  like enticement of flame (L44 nuke) but not like the full &quot;lure&quot; series.  To put it in perspective, shrieker's curse is &quot;lure 1&quot; with the same modifier, and with 150ish of that resist you can resist it reliably (well,  last patched messed with this <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ). <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lythe>Lythe</A> at: 9/16/02 7:16:40 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ubeckerrivenblade.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Becker Rivenblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/16/02 7:06:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3890.topic&index=5>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Resists on Rage of Vallon</span><hr size=1> Before the patch, RoV was sticking on the sentries alot, but now it hardly ever does.  I think it had a lot of partial resists on the damage, which now translate to full resists.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udralsmashbonk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dral Smashbonk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 45<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/16/02 8:58:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3890.topic&index=6>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Resists on Rage of Vallon</span><hr size=1> Bellowing Winds... the obnoxious AE of lady nev has that same magic(-100) resist listing in lucy, but I hardly resisted it with 290+ MR (depending where the bard was standing)<br>
